<paragraph id="C36DB15443BFFACBF726FB820913EC06" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="7E0DEAFABE173912F4D8BD9980F7279F" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
A species with a disjunct distribution closely paralleling that of 
<taxonomicName id="ED70821A6788F177DE93A9523B30018B" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Ipomoea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pubescens">
<emphasis id="6754172BC90F77A775CC800EB900AC23" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Ipomoea pubescens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, being found in Colombia, Peru, Bolivia and Argentina in South America and the United States and Mexico in North America. It is characteristic of open stony hillsides with subpuna vegetation between 2400 and 4000 m, the lower altitudes recorded from the extreme south and the extreme north of its range. It usually grows in small populations, often only a single plant being found.
</paragraph>
